      "description": "A traditional Scottish soup transformed with hearty bulgur wheat and lamb.",
      "recipeIngredient": [
        "2 lbs. lamb shoulder",
        "8 cups water",
        "1/2 cup bulgur wheat",
        "1 cup diced carrots",
        "1 cup diced turnip",
        "1 cup chopped leeks",
        "1/2 cup pearl barley",
        "Salt and pepper to taste",
        "Fresh parsley for garnish"
      ],
      "recipeInstructions": [
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "text": "In a large pot, add lamb and water. Bring to a boil and skim off any foam."
        },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "text": "Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour until lamb is tender."
        },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "text": "Remove lamb, shred meat, and return to pot."
        },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "text": "Add bulgur wheat, barley, carrots, turnip, and leeks."
        },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "text": "Simmer for 45 minutes until grains and vegetables are tender."
        },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "text": "Season with salt and pepper."
        },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
